Here's a link to WoW's rep system

I’ve been waiting about 3 years for 2.2 in gd
Darkmoon Faire will take a while because it happens once a month
It happens the first Sunday of every month and lasts 1 week
One week isn't bad unless you're really busy.
Ravenholdt is an old unfinished rep from Vanilla, the only way to get rep with it is to farm Syndicate NPCs in older zones
You'll get about 5 rep or so per kill
And finally, getting honored with the Buccaneers and the 4 reps known as the "Steamwheedle Cartel"
Completing a single quest for Booty Bay (which most people have probably done before starting this achievement) instantly makes you hated with the Buccaneers
The only way to get rep with them is to kill guards in Booty Bay.  These guys are designed as anti-PvP bouncers, so they hit hard and take a while to kill.
They give 25 rep per kill.  You gotta do this until you hit honored with the pirates
You will save yourself a lot of time by using a character who hasn't touched the cartel reps
All I'm hearing is BS everywhere.
And when you finally hit honored with the pirates, you gotta start killing THEM :D
And earn enough rep to get Exalted with the entire Cartel, which probably has you at 35,999 / 36,000 hated rep
But yeah, the entire point of the achievement is that you'd have to be insane to attempt the amount of grind necessary
Which is also why it's a Feat of Strength and isn't listed unless you manage to earn it
It's kind of like these essence achievements this expansion
I'm not sure if I'm ever going to return to raiding in WoW
Depending on your guild, it's basically signing up for 4 - 9 hours of gameplay a week
But this one essence ability you can earn requires you to get these items from the final boss of a wing in the Eternal Palace raid
It takes 9 items for rank 1, 18 for rank 2, and 36 for rank 3
There are 3 bosses total that drop them per week
If you do solely LFR, it will take you 21 weeks to get all 3 ranks. 3 for 1, 6 for 2, and 12 for 3.
And I though NieR: Automata on the hardest difficultly was bad.
BUT, if you raid on anything else, it goes much faster
Normal will net you 3 items per boss :D
But for most people, Heroic will be the highest they go
Assuming you full clear the raid every week, you can get 21 items per week
It takes 63 items to achieve rank 3.  So it will take 3 weeks to get that
In short, I'm too old for this bs. And I'm 19.
If you have extra traits for other specializations, they will only require 1/3 the items once you max the first
So it goes down to 21 for each additional rank 3.  AKA 1 more week per
To do anything above LFR requires a committment to a large group of people :/
so... uh... you do have fun with wow, right?
Oh, definitely.  I'm just finding that my priorities are switching :D
Just pointing out that the game has gotten super grindy
At least, relative to me now that I don't raid
You know how we have streams on Friday / Sunday at set times?
Raiding more or less is that. A good example would be a guild raiding Friday, Saturday, and maybe Sunday from 8 - 11, 11 - 2, 10 - 12, etc
Wash rinse repeat.  Huge time committment
Morning to night or night to morning?
You could always try using the LFG tool to do dungeons, but you'll spend a lot of time trying to get into a group, and success isn't guaranteed
Very few guilds raid in the morning
11 - 2 seems extreme, but the other two time slots seem alright.
Hehe, that's a time I used to raid
I'm a bit of a night owl ;)
Sadly, I don't want to do 11 - 2, or 12 - 3
Midnight is when I call it.
The latter is too close to when I sleep.  11 - 2 would require me to book it out of work when my shift ends, eat quickly, and then spend most of the rest of my night doing that raid
And raiding CAN be fun, but if you get tired of it, you gotta decide whether or not you want to keep doing it :/
Skip out too much, and your group will start looking for a replacement
Luckily, there's plenty to do in WoW!
And then you forget everything or something changes where you have to relearn the controls.
LFR let's you experience a very watered down version of raids, experience the story
TBH, it's not necessarily a bad thing that some things are so grindy
IF all you play is WoW, and you've got the free time you're willing to burn, it's like any other time sink game
But some games do it better than others.
Also, WoW is NOT a game for completionists.  A lot of achievements require serious committments to certain aspects of gameplay
For example, you're not likely to be a Mythic raider while at the same time a top-rated PvPer
Not unless you stream or create WoW content and it's your job
The game will probably be less grindy next expansion
They're done with artifact systems after this expansion.  They're dialing back RNG on gear drops
Part of the reason I'm dialing back (or trying to) my WoW playtime is that I want to play other games
